The user is saying that newly added operators are not showing up in the "Kunduzgi Smena" and "Tungi Smena" tables in the MasterPanel. Let me look at the MasterPanel code again.

Looking at the MasterPanel code, the issue is in how operators are filtered for display in the shift tables:

```jsx
{operators.map(op => {
    const opAsgs = kunduzAssignments.filter(a => a.operator_id === op.id && a.is_active === 1);
    const resting = isResting(op.id);
    if (opAsgs.length === 0) return null;


```

So operators only show up in the shift tables if they have active assignments. The user wants operators to be visible even without assignments, grouped by their shift type. I need to modify the filtering logic so that operators appear in their respective shift tables regardless of whether they have assignments, and then display their assignments if they exist.

Updating the filtering logic...

